12/04/2007
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- In a letter to the government Wednesday (April 11th), European Commission (EC) President Jose Manuel Barroso reiterated the EC's continuing efforts in the case of the five Bulgarian nurses and one Palestinian doctor, sentenced to death following a controversial HIV infection trial in Libya. 
Barroso assured Bulgarians that they could rely on solidarity from the EU in efforts to release the six medics. 
(Darik - 12/04/07; Bulgarian Government website, News.bg - 11/04/07)
